Reporting the Generated Rubric
The final rubric pack should include:

the value proposition and decision context;
selected criteria and programme-specific definitions;
subcriteria and judgement questions;
poor, adequate, good, and excellent standards;
evidence plan and source traceability;
treatment of monetised and non-monetised value;
treatment of alternatives, risk, uncertainty, distribution, and affordability;
known evidence gaps and confidence implications;
synthesis approach for the final VfI judgement.

The rubric is ready to use when an evaluator can explain, before reviewing the evidence, what would count as poor, adequate, good, or excellent resource use and what evidence would support each judgement.
